commit_message:
Updated boro

Boro.csv now includes cumulative data from start of outbreak.

Update summary.csv

Language change re: hospitalizations

Updated summary.csv

Updated reference to estimated hospitalizations

Added testing data

Added testing data and updated Readme to include testing data and clarify time period through which most recent data may be incomplete.

Added tests-by-zcta.csv

Added cumulative tests by ZCTA data, and updated Readme with notes.

Update README.md

Clarified ZIP of residence for tests by ZIP data.

Update with 4/1 data

Boro.csv file modified to include case counts as well as rates.

Delete testing.csv

Testing data will be on NYC Open Data going forward.

Update case-hosp-death.csv

Fixing header label issue.

Added probable-confirmed-dod.csv

Added data on probable covid-19 deaths by date of death, and updated Readme to include information on this new file.

Update README.md

Added documentation on sources for New York State reports of deaths in NYC, and difference with NYC DOHMH reports.

4/27 data update

Includes fix to yesterday's column-header change to tests-by-zcta.csv

4/29 data update

Includes moving probable-confirmed-dod.csv into a Deaths folder

Update probable-confirmed-dod.csv

Fixed error in 5/9 commit that had msilabeled data for 5/8/2020.

5/11 data update

Today's update includes new reports of approximately 3600 cases that previously had missing addresses. These cases were diagnosed earlier in the epidemic and do not reflect recently diagnosed patients.

5/17 data upload

Added updated file with correct date formatting

5/18 data update

This update includes major data additions, including data-by-modzcta, Boro/, Deaths/ syndromic_data, tests, and more. Previous files that included rates (boro, by-age, by-sex) now also include counts. Major additions to Readme offer more technical notes on these data.

Delete probable-confirmed-dod.csv

All death files moved to deaths/

Fix problem with probable-confirmed-dod.csv

Initial upload left out the "probable" column of this file. Uploading a fixed version.

06/01 data update

Updated data-by-modzcta with new neighborhood names. Previous names were UHF42 parent-neighborhood names. New names come from the Neighborhood Organizing Census Committee. See Readme for more.

Update README.md

Added detail on hospitalization sources.

6/9 data upload

Starting with 6/9 data upload, data-by-modzcta.csv includes content that was previously included in the tests-by-zcta.csv file. Moving forward, the tests-by-zcta.csv will no longer be updated.

Add files via upload

Due to improvements in address information, data cleaning, and classification procedures on records of people who have died from COVID-19, today's data upload includes changes to values for cumulative deaths by geography, and to counts of death by date of death.
